  "handoff_packets": [
    {
      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 0,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"outcome_review\",\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: outcome_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nWhen panel reviewers DISAGREE \\u2014 or all accept but a minority objection is strong \\u2014 route the strongest objection through a separate tool-backed ADJUDICATION packet over the exact findings, refs, hashes, and tests, recovering minority-but-correct verdicts instead of vote-counting. (Grounded in reasoning-tree auditing, arXiv:2602.09341.)\\n\\nSCOPE (do):\\n1. Detect disagreement / strong-minority-objection across independent_reviewer_results[].\\n2. Assemble an adjudication packet: the strongest objection + its evidence refs/hashes/tests; run a bounded, tool-backed adjudication that inspects the cited evidence (not a majority count).\\n3. The adjudicated outcome can BLOCK or ESCALATE; a real revise/deny still hard-blocks; surface the strongest objection on the verdict.\\n\\nNON-GOALS: do NOT resolve by majority vote; do NOT add calibrated weighting (next slice); do NOT weaken any block.\\n\\nACCEPTANCE:\\n- A split panel triggers adjudication over the cited refs/hashes/tests.\\n- A minority-but-correct objection can block/escalate (not silently outvoted).\\n- A real revise/deny still BLOCKS; deterministic replay; full suite green; ledger + replay artifacts exported.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-adjudication-20260601/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"8a24db8ca0493545b1c7f432bf8c97b2b63b514434aa83484ddb83b6206ecd44\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-adjudication-20260601/source/grill-findings.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"c9a2d7395c50b188b0326d1af63dec00eebcac0e4ad27a01d85c53a5fe0a2e99\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"issues\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-adjudication-20260601/source/issues.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"f5157897d35ad1c2d86297db3b901dd28ab5b088a1bc62b734e4510a5db310d7\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"tdd_plan\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-adjudication-20260601/source/tdd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"af64adbf43579308638fb7ea388b2b57f9172476c3392427b666a0dcf3981cd8\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-adjudication-20260601/source/grill-findings-tdd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"d10d3d639705072477c817c688b2dc0faa8fbb6f872869cea105abf90872ec9f\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"implement